Key Match Events: The Netherlands amassed 158 for 4 after being asked to bat first, with Tom Cooper’s quickfire 35 off 19 balls followed by Colin Ackermann’s unbeaten 41 off 26 deliveries.
Pre-Game Insights: A win would have been enough for South Africa to claim at least a top-two spot in their Super 12s group.
Post-Match Reflections: Temba Bavuma admitted it is a label that will stick after this latest setback.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Netherlands, the lowest ranked team to reach this stage, pulling off a famous win allowed Pakistan to leapfrog South Africa to reach the semi-finals after beating Bangladesh later on Sunday.
Others: The loss therefore signals a sudden end to Mark Boucher’s tenure as South Africa head coach although he was more measured about whether his side badly lost their nerve.
